                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[The iPad Mini With an A17 Pro Chip Is Just $379 Today]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/the-ipad-mini-with-an-a17-pro-chip-is-just-379-today/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/apple-ipad-mini-7.jpg" length="1430" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple iPad mini (2024)]]></category><category><![CDATA[Deals]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            There's a huge discount on the newest iPad Mini.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>You can get the newest Apple iPad Mini for an incredible <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0DK3YF38G/?tag=hotoge-20&ascsubtag=UUhtgUeUpU2017166&asc_refurl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.howtogeek.com%2Fthe-ipad-mini-with-an-a17-pro-chip-is-just-379-today%2F&asc_campaign=Affiliate" rel="noopener noreferrer sponsored nofollow" target="_blank" class="norewrite noskim">$379.00 on Amazon</a> for a limited time. This is a 24% discount from its original price of $499.00, making this a great price for the latest version of Apple's tablet.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 07 Oct 2025 16:57:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/the-ipad-mini-with-an-a17-pro-chip-is-just-379-today/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Python 3.14 Has Arrived With T-String Support]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/python-314-has-arrived-with-t-string-support/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/python-logo-over-blurred-python-code-background-with-the-word-python-written-in-yellow-underneath.png" length="2949" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Programming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Python]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Template string literals are finally coming to Python, and other improvements.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Python 3.14 is officially here, and brings a mix of changes to the core language, the interpreter's guts, and the standard library. These are major updates like template string literals, deferred evaluation of annotations, and even official support for subinterpreters in the standard library.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 07 Oct 2025 16:44:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/python-314-has-arrived-with-t-string-support/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[8 Useful Things You Can Plug Into Your Car's OBD2 Port]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/useful-things-you-can-plug-into-your-cars-obd2-port/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Cory Gunther]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/illustration-showing-a-car-s-interior-with-a-highlighted-obd-port-surrounded-by-devices-like-the-bluedriver-dongle-a-car-hud-and-the-scangauge-display.png" length="2115" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Automotive]]></category><category><![CDATA[Electric Vehicles]]></category><category><![CDATA[DIY]]></category><category><![CDATA[iPhone]]></category><category><![CDATA[SUVs]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Plug in all the things. 
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Have you ever looked under your car's steering wheel at all the wires, fuses, and plugs? If so, you might find an odd plug called an OBD-II port. That's the same port any technician uses during a smog test, and mechanics access it to scan for check engine light errors, but that's not all it can do. You can plug several useful or weird things into that 16-pin port. </p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 07 Oct 2025 16:30:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/useful-things-you-can-plug-into-your-cars-obd2-port/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[From Snatch to Adolescence: 12 of Stephen Graham’s Best Roles Ever]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/stephen-graham-best-film-television-roles/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Keeley Brooks]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/collage-of-stephen-graham-in-a-thousand-blows-adolescence-boardwalk-empire-and-boiling-point.png" length="2693" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[TV Shows]]></category><category><![CDATA[ Movies]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Adolescence]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            See how the esteemed actor evolved into an award-winning powerhouse.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Esteemed British actor Stephen Graham is finally seeing the stardom he has long deserved. The chameleon of talent recently won his first Primetime Emmy for his role in the hit <a href="https://www.netflix.com/" target="_blank">Netflix</a> psycho-drama series <em>Adolescence</em>. Weeks prior to its release, Graham snatched viewers’ attention with his powerhouse portrayal of 19th-century boxer Sugar Goodson in <a href="https://disneyplus.bn5x.net/c/156932/564546/9358?subId1=UUhtgUeUpU2017108&subId2=ehtg&u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hulu.com%2Fwelcome&ourl=http%3A%2F%2Fhulu.com%2F" class="norewrite noskim" rel="sponsored nofollow" target="_blank">Hulu</a>’s <em>A Thousand Blows</em>.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 07 Oct 2025 16:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/stephen-graham-best-film-television-roles/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Notepad++ Just Got an Update With a New Clipboard Trick]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/notebook-got-an-update-heres-whats-new/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/notepad-logo-on-a-blue-background.jpg" length="41" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Notepad++]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Making Notepad++ even better.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Notepad++ just dropped version 8.8.6, and now you can finally paste multiple lines of text directly into the Find and Replace fields. You no longer have to rely on workarounds or plugins for multi-line text manipulation, among other fixes.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 07 Oct 2025 15:33:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/notebook-got-an-update-heres-whats-new/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[This is Why You Should Replace Your ISP's Router ASAP]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/this-is-why-you-should-replace-your-isps-router-asap/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Timothy Jacob Hudson]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/tp-link-archer-be9700-tri-band-wi-fi-7-router-on-a-table.jpg" length="452" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Web]]></category><category><![CDATA[Wi-Fi Routers]]></category><category><![CDATA[internet]]></category><category><![CDATA[Hardware]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            There are a lot of reasons you should buy your own router instead of using the one your internet provider gives you.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>When you buy service from an internet provider, they usually give you a router to go along with it. You might be inclined to use this router instead of going out to buy your own, but trust me: there are many reasons to ignore that ISP router.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 07 Oct 2025 15:30:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/this-is-why-you-should-replace-your-isps-router-asap/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Firefox Is Stealing Another Chrome Feature]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/firefox-is-stealing-another-chrome-feature/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Arol Wright]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/firefox-logo-at-the-center-with-fire-surrounding-the-image.jpg" length="1627" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Web]]></category><category><![CDATA[Firefox]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            If it's fully implemented, it could be awesome.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Mozilla's Firefox is one of the few non-Chromium browsers that exist these days, and it remains one of the most solid browser options out there. But that doesn't mean that it's not allowed to take a page or two from Chrome every so often. Now, it has just got a pretty useful Google feature that you might like.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 07 Oct 2025 15:18:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/firefox-is-stealing-another-chrome-feature/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[This Logitech Mouse Cured My Wrist Pain—and It's 17% Off for Prime Day]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/the-logitech-mx-master-3s-cured-my-wrist-pain-for-goodand-its-17-off-for-prime-day/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/52909920835_5cf85c4403_o.jpg" length="185" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Mac]]></category><category><![CDATA[Deals]]></category><category><![CDATA[Amazon Prime Day 2025]]></category><category><![CDATA[Amazon Prime Day]]></category><category><![CDATA[Logitech]]></category><category><![CDATA[mouse]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            A legendary mouse for even less.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>My first MX Master mouse was the second-generation model, and that transformed my struggle with wrist pain as someone who (like many of you) has to work in front of a computer all day. When my first MX Master mouse wore out, I upgraded to the MX Master 3S, and my wrist pain has never returned.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 07 Oct 2025 15:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/the-logitech-mx-master-3s-cured-my-wrist-pain-for-goodand-its-17-off-for-prime-day/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[It’s Now Illegal for Commercials to Be Too Loud in This State]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/its-now-illegal-for-commercials-to-be-too-loud-in-this-state/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/shutterstock_1966720738.jpg" length="408" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Streaming]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Now it's time for more states to adopt the same legislature.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>California just signed a new law, Senate Bill 576. This is going to force streaming services like Netflix, Hulu, and Amazon Prime Video to stop blasting loud, jarring commercials that are way louder than the shows you're actually watching.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 07 Oct 2025 15:03:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/its-now-illegal-for-commercials-to-be-too-loud-in-this-state/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[How to Crop Pictures in Microsoft Word, Excel, and PowerPoint]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/crop-pictures-microsoft-word-excel-powerpoint/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Tony Phillips]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/3d-illustration-of-microsoft-excel-word-powerpoint-and-image-icons-floating-on-a-blue-background-with-a-crop-and-resize-tool-overlay-in-front.png" length="1437" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Microsoft]]></category><category><![CDATA[Microsoft 365]]></category><category><![CDATA[Microsoft Office]]></category><category><![CDATA[image editing]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Edit images in Microsoft's popular productivity programs.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Whether you want to focus on a particular part of a picture, remove distracting detail from the edges of a graphic, or reshape an image to fit a specific layout, the Crop tool in Microsoft Word, Excel, and PowerPoint is a useful and versatile feature. Here's how to use it.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 07 Oct 2025 15:00:36 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/crop-pictures-microsoft-word-excel-powerpoint/</guid></item></channel>
